import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.strftime('%Y')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Total', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the trend of electricity consumption in Iowa over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Electricity Consumption (MWh)')
    plt.axhline(y=data['Total'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Consumption')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    sns.histplot(data=data, x='residential', kde=True, color='blue')

    plt.title('What is the distribution of residential electricity consumption in Iowa?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Residential Electricity Consumption (kWh)')

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x="Commercial", y="Industrial", data=data, color='blue')
    ax.set_title('What is the correlation between commercial and industrial electricity consumption in Iowa?', wrap=True)
    ax.axhline(data['Industrial'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Industrial Mean')
    ax.axvline(data['Commercial'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Commercial Mean')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x="Year", y="Consumption per capita (kWh)", data=data, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the average electricity consumption per capita in Iowa?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['Consumption per capita (kWh)'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Consumption')
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='state', y='rate', data=data, color='lightblue')
    plt.title('Distribution of Electricity Rates in Iowa', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Electricity Rate')
    plt.axhline(y=data['rate'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["rate"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
